                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d666">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">394.115 Panay/172: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-12-21T17:00:00+01:00"
                            >December 21, 1937—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 21—2:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>528. My telegram 527, December 21, 1 p.m.<note n="94" xml:id="d666fn94">Not
                        printed.</note> I find that in an earlier despatch describing the death of
                    Sandri which was printed in the <hi rend="italic">Corriere Delia Sera</hi> of
                    December 18, and which has just been brought to my attention Barzini reported as
                    follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“The boats were returning to the ship to get medicines and distilled
                            water when boats full of troops which had been lying wait on the other
                            bank during the bombardment approached the <hi rend="italic">Panay</hi>
                            which was slowly disappearing under water and opened fire with machine
                            guns on the deserted vessel.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
